item.description: Biography I am a masters student in the Psychology Department at the University of Oregon. I am broadly interested in understanding how people make decisions in different situations. What external and internal evaluations are made when making a “mundane” choice versus a “serious” choice? How might situational constraints (such as time, exhaustion, stress, novelty, etc) affect what actually gets considered when making a decision, and are there individual differences that can predict the adoption of certain decision strategies over others?
